<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>  <legaldoc><law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection chaptername="Railroads" statutenumber="74-921"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>74-921</statuteno><catchline>Locomotive operators; conductors; intoxication; penalty.</catchline><para>Any person who is intoxicated while in charge of a locomotive running upon the track of any railroad or while acting as the conductor of a car or train of cars on any railroad shall be guilty of a Class I misdemeanor.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>R.S.1866, c. 25, &#167; 108, p. 227; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 6057; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 5414; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 74-706; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 74-706; </para><para>Laws 1977, LB 39, &#167; 188; </para><para>R.S.1943, (1990), &#167; 74-706; </para><para>Laws 1994, LB 414, &#167; 21. </para></source></law></legaldoc> 